This paper deals with the problem of causality and correlation in machine learning, which is a common topic in the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also examines the cognitive abilities of human experts and non-experts, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which is a popular technique in computer vision (cs.CY) and neural engineering (cs.NE).
